tegory scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="God is in the Little Things" /><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Interview" /><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="interview feature" /><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Jo Linsdell" /><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Patricia Brooks" /><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="writers" /><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="writers and authors" /><title type="text">Interview with Patricia Brooks</title><content type="html">&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-Bfh5bQJkA_M/VD-hxflA0CI/AAAAAAAAR5Q/U0gdfZKY-oA/s1600/MessagesfromtheGoldenAngels_Cover.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: right; float: right; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 1em;"&gt;&lt;img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-Bfh5bQJkA_M/VD-hxflA0CI/AAAAAAAAR5Q/U0gdfZKY-oA/s1600/MessagesfromtheGoldenAngels_Cover.jpg" height="320" width="211" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;What genre do you write and why?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;My genre is spiritual.&amp;nbsp; My books are my honest, raw, and emotional retelling of my true spiritual experiences and I have been Divinely guided to write and share them.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12.0pt; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-margin-top-alt: auto;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; line-height: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB"&gt;Tell us about your latest book.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;My new book &lt;i&gt;God is in the Little Things: Messages from the Golden Angels &lt;/i&gt;is the continuation of my true spiritual journey. I share from my heart deep lessons I have learned. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;It reveals my struggle to reclaim my connection to my Higher Self and discover the meaning of my life. Through it you can travel with me through my past lives from Ancient Rome to the cobblestone streets of &lt;st1:city w:st="on"&gt;&lt;st1:place w:st="on"&gt;Boston&lt;/st1:place&gt;&lt;/st1:city&gt;. Cry with me as I share the intimate details of my struggles and how I learn to heal my broken heart. Spiritual revelations unfold before your eyes as I discover the true meaning of life and I begin living my new life with clarity and purpose. Watch as I move from wounded and weak to a powerful and empowered spiritual being.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12pt; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12.0pt; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-margin-top-alt: auto;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; line-height: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB"&gt;What marketing methods are you using to promote your book?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;I promote my book through social media and have a presence on Facebook, Twitter, Google+, LinkedIn and Spiritual Networks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;I am also building my email list with a free gift on my website.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;Additionally I am grateful for the opportunity to have reviewers and bloggers share information on me and my work as we are doing now.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;Most importantly I am building long term relationships with people through these connections and through my radio show, not only with my guests, but with my listeners too.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12.0pt; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12.0pt; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-margin-top-alt: auto;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; line-height: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB"&gt;What's your favourite quote about writing/for writers?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;The first quote that comes to mind is a silly one and is from the Keep Calm series… Keep Calm and Press Delete!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12pt; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12.0pt; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-margin-top-alt: auto;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; line-height: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB"&gt;What's the best thing about being a writer?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;The best thing for me about being a writer is that I can go deep within myself and not only re-examine my experiences for my own spiritual growth, but I can share my experiences with others and hopefully help them on their spiritual path too.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12pt; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12.0pt; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-margin-top-alt: auto;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; line-height: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB"&gt;Where can people find out more about you and your writing?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;I would love for readers to visit my website &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.patriciabrooks.net/" style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;www.patriciabrooks.net&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;where they can find out more about me, my books, read my blogs, listen to my radio show and more.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;I would also welcome reader emails to discuss whatever is on their mind as they walk their spiritual path and suggestions for guests or topics they would like to hear on my radio show &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i style="line-height: 12pt;"&gt;Spiritual Lens with Rev. Patricia Brooks.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-I49IwNwdlC4/VD-h212o2nI/AAAAAAAAR5Y/AB66oA7pEXU/s1600/PatriciaBrooks_CTR250.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"&gt;&lt;img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-I49IwNwdlC4/VD-h212o2nI/AAAAAAAAR5Y/AB66oA7pEXU/s1600/PatriciaBrooks_CTR250.jpg" height="200" width="182" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;Why do you thi&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;nk readers are going to enjoy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt; your book?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;Readers whether seasoned spiritual seekers or new to their spiritual journey, are telling me that my story touched them so deeply because it is as if I am speaking from their soul.&amp;nbsp; Many have expressed that emotions have surfaced from deep within themselves and they have wept while reading it. &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;I know that the spiritual experiences I have had and continue to have, are not unique to me and whether or not you have experienced past life regressions or channels or healings etc, your Higher Self is always communicating with you and you feel the stirrings in your soul to respond.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;Where can a reader purchase your book?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;Autographed copies of my books can be purchased from me through my website &lt;a href="http://www.patriciabrooks.net/"&gt;www.patriciabrooks.net&lt;/a&gt; or copies can be purchased from &lt;a href="http://www.amazon.com/"&gt;www.amazon.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;What books or authors have most influenced your life?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;Seat of the Soul&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt; by Gary Zukav and &lt;i&gt;Conversations with God&lt;/i&gt;by Neale Donald Walsh are incredible.&amp;nbsp; I am also reading &lt;i&gt;My Greatest Love, My Greatest Sorrow&lt;/i&gt; by Johanna Carroll and &lt;i&gt;Convoluted Universe &lt;/i&gt;by Dolores Cannon.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;When you’re not writing, how do you spend your time?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;My spiritual journey has taken me from living life solely through my disconnected ego mind, to wanting to only connect spiritually and almost abandoning the physical life around me, to finally and gratefully understanding the true gift of being a Spiritual being in this human form we take on.&amp;nbsp; Conscious of the opportunity to experience the physical as a spiritual being I love to spend time outside in nature, taking my dog for a walk, having coffee with friends, the simple things.&amp;nbsp; &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.jolinsdell.com/" title="Jo Linsdell"&gt;&lt;img alt="blogsignatureWA" src="http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8176/8030439972_551fda411e.jpg" height="120" width="500" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;script src="//s7.addthis.com/js/300/addthis_widget.js#pubid=xa-51adb6a4646b451d" type="text/javascript"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;document.doAT = function(cl) {         var myclass = new RegExp('hentry');         var myTitleContainer = new RegExp('post-title');         var myPostContent = new RegExp('post-footer');         var elem = this.getElementsByTagName('div');            var url;         var title = "";                  for (var i = 0; i &lt; elem.length; i++)         {             var classes = elem[i].className;             if (myclass.test(classes))             {                 var container = elem[i];              url = window.location.href;                               for (var b = 0; b &lt; container.childNodes.length; b++)                 {                     var item = container.childNodes[b].className;                     if (myTitleContainer.test(item))                     {                         var link = container.childNodes[b].getElementsByTagName('a');                         if (typeof(link[0]) != 'undefined')                         {                             var url = link[0].href;                             var title = link[0].innerHTML;                         }                      var singleq = new RegExp("'", 'g');                     var doubleq = new RegExp('"', 'g');                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             title = title.replace(singleq, ''', 'gi');                     title = title.replace(doubleq, '"', 'gi');                      }                     if (myPostContent.test(item))                     {                         var footer = container.childNodes[b];                     }                 }                  var n = document.createElement('div');                  var at = "&lt;div class='addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style ' addthis:title='"+title+"' addthis:url='"+encodeURI(url)+"'   &gt; &lt;a class='addthis_button_facebook_like' fb:like:layout='button_count'&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class='addthis_button_tweet'&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class='addthis_button_pinterest_pinit'&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class='addthis_counter addthis_pill_style'&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/div&gt;";                  n.innerHTML = at;                  container.insertBefore(n , footer);                }         }     return true; };  document.doAT('hentry'); &lt;/script&gt;&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-count="none" data-via="jolinsdell"&gt;Tweet&lt;/a&gt;&lt;script type="text/javascript" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

